headline: US stocks open mixed at the end of a holiday-shortened week
summary: Stocks are mostly flat in quiet trading Friday as investors returned from the Christmas holiday.  The S&P 500 index was up less than 0.1% as of 10 a.m. ET, the Dow Jones Industrial Average was roughly unchanged, and the Nasdaq composite was down less than 0.1%.  The big institutional investors are largely closed out of their positions for the year.
